Lab:-(local machine)
# mkdir mumbaigit	(To create directory)
# cd mumbaigit		(To enter directory)
# git init		(to initialize folder as a Repository)	
# cat >any filename 	(To creating a file for demo)
# git status		(To check status)
# git add . 		(To Add all data on current directory)
# git add <filename/path to file> (single or space separated multiple file )
# git status		(To check status)
# git commit -m "write something" 	(for commit)
# git status 		(check status)
# git log		(To check log)	  
# git show <commit id>	(To check all changes

# git remote add origin <github repo URL>	(to add URL as a default for the current repo)
# git push -u origin <Branch name> 		(Branch name can be "main or anything" )
[now enter username & Personal access token]
Personal access token path:- github-console > setting > Developer setting > Personal access tokens > Generate token  (Only for Linux)
# git status 

Download any repo from github.com to our local machine :- 
1. Go to the particular repo in github.com
2. Copy the URL from the CODE button (https URL)
3. Now create a new folder on your local machine &  go inside the folder 
4. Open git bash by right click  

$ sudo git clone <paste the github repo URL>

For pulling new changes write :-
$ sudo git pull <paste the github repo URL>



